Barn: Gösta Lennart f. 27. — Stud:ex. 20, stud. v. hand:-högsk. i Köln 20-21 o. i Engl. 23. Tjg. på sv. gen :konsulatet i Marseille 21-22, dir. i firma Neico G. Jeansson & Co. i Hamburg 24-28, num. disp. f. Margarin A-B Svea. Nederländernas v. konsul i Kalmar sed. 29. Led. av styr. f. hamndirekt. o. Margarin A-B Svea samt Margarinbol. i Sthlm, verkst. dir. o. ordf. i styr. f. Kom-manditbol. Ragnar L. Jeansson & Söner, led. av styr. f. A-B Liva Fa’br. Kapt. i SVK. RNedOiNO, SVKGM, SFMKSM, Nederländsk SM, Deutsche Trainkreuz.
translated: Jeansson, Gösta Theodor, Deputy Consul, Kalmar, b. 21/2/01 in Kalmar to Director Ragnar J. and Tyra Bruun. Married to Ann-Marie Ericson. Children: Gösta Lennart b. 27. Graduated high school 1920, studied at the University of Business and Economics in Cologne 1920-1921 and in England 1923. Served at the Swedish Consulate General in Marseille 1921-1922, director at the firm Neico G. Jeansson & Co. in Hamburg 1924-1928, nominated representative for Margarin A-B Svea. Deputy Consul in the Netherlands in Kalmar since 1929. Board member of the Port Authority and Margarin A-B Svea, as well as Margarinbol. in Stockholm. Managing director and chairman of the board for the joint-stock company Ragnar L. Jeansson & Sons, board member of A-B Liva Fa'br. Captain in the Swedish Volunteer Corps. Awards: Royal Dutch Order of Orange-Nassau, Swedish Royal Merit Medal in gold, Swedish Gold Medal for Merit in Field and Coastal Defense, Dutch Silver Medal, and German Military Service Cross.
